article.headline: Harvard 72, Columbia 63
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Jeremy Lin and Keith Wright each scored 14 points as Harvard slipped by Columbia 72-63 on Friday night. Lin added nine rebounds and five assists while Wright had six rebounds and four blocks for Harvard (12-13, 4-7 Ivy League Conference). Noruwa Agho had 13 points and Niko Scott added 12 to lead Columbia (11-14, 6-5 Ivy League Conference), which lost its second straight game after winning six of seven. Trailing 35-33 with 16:22 to play, Harvard went on a 23-6 run over the next eight and a half minutes to take a 56-41 lead. Columbia pulled to within six, 58-52, with 4:21 to play, but Harvard made 12-of-14 free throws down the stretch. Harvard's Drew Housman, who finished with six steals, combined with Oliver McNally to score Harvards final seven points over the last 1:08.
